lback method using ID or name for better coverage. I’ll consider these options moving forward!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating method structure**\\n\\nI'm working on implementing a simple SearchContext, which seems good. However, I realize that direct dynamic coverage builder isn't guaranteed in native environments. That’s fine, though—I can still make it work. I need to check if I should import `java.lang.reflect.Proxy` or `InvocationHandler`. Wait, is using direct reflection not necessary? Hmm, I should edit my approach to clarify this. Let's see how best to proceed!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xbGEv7sNdHbsnOPHNXWjiRy0|fc_0e887a5a86dbbe14016a2580e629f48196b478a329fb9a3f40", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0/src/test/java/org_seleniumhq_selenium/selenium_support/AnnotationsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.openqa.selenium.By;\nimport org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;\n", "newText": "import org.openqa.selenium.By;\nimport org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext;\nimport org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void buildByInstantiatesFindByBuilderFromPageFactoryFinderAnnotation() throws NoSuchFieldException {\n        Field field = SearchPage.class.getDeclaredField(\"submitButton\");\n\n        By locator = new Annotations(field).buildBy();\n\n        assertThat(locator.toString()).isEqualTo(\"By.id: submit-button\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class SearchPage {\n        @FindBy(id = \"submit-button\")\n        private WebElement submitButton;\n    }\n", "newText": "    void buildByCreatesLocatorForFindByAnnotatedField() throws NoSuchFieldException {\n        Field field = SearchPage.class.getDeclaredField(\"submitButton\");\n        RecordingSearchContext context = new RecordingSearchContext();\n\n        By locator = new Annotations(field).buildBy();\n        List<WebElement> elements = locator.findElements(context);\n\n        assertThat(elements).isSameAs(context.elements);\n        assertThat(context.locators).contains(\"By.id: submitButton\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class SearchPage {\n        @FindBy(id = \"submitButton\")\n        private WebElement submitButton;\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingSearchContext implements SearchContext {\n        private final List<WebElement> elements = List.of();\n        private final List<String> locators = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        @Override\n        public List<WebElement> findElements(By by) {\n            locators.add(by.toString());\n            return elements;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public WebElement findElement(By by) {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"Single-element lookup is not used by this test\");\n        }\n    }\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0/src/test/java/org_seleniumhq_selenium/selenium_support/AnnotationsTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"import java.lang.reflect.Field;\\n\",\"newText\":\"import java.lang.reflect.Field;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"import org.openqa.selenium.By;\\nimport org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;\\n\",\"newText\":\"import org.openqa.selenium.By;\\nimport org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext;\\nimport org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"    void buildByInstantiatesFindByBuilderFromPageFactoryFinderAnnotation() throws NoSuchFieldException {\\n        Field field = SearchPage.class.getDeclaredField(\\\"submitButton\\\");\\n\\n        By locator = new Annotations(field).buildBy();\\n\\n        assertThat(locator.toString()).isEqualTo(\\\"By.id: submit-button\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class SearchPage {\\n        @FindBy(id = \\\"submit-button\\\")\\n        private 